# Database Design Rules

- Use UUID as PK for all tables.
- Enforce ENUM values exactly as defined in guide (e.g., incident status: pending | assigned | investigating | closed | escalated).
- Chain-of-custody must be stored as JSONB with officer ID, timestamp, and reason.
- Apply foreign keys for all relationships (incident → docket → arrest → warrant → evidence).
